@baseUrl = http://localhost:8096

###
### Paste API Tests
### Controller: PasteApiController
### Validation: @NotBlank and @Size on content field in PasteRequest, @Valid on request body
### Response: Returns PasteResponse JSON on success (200 OK)
### Error format: JSON {"error": "message"} for validation/not found errors
###

### Create paste - Basic text
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/paste
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Hello World",
  "content": "Hello, world! This is a test paste.",
  "language": "TEXT",
  "expiration": "1h",
  "isPrivate": false
}

### Create paste - Code with syntax highlighting
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/paste
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Kotlin Example",
  "content": "fun main() {\n    println(\"Hello, Kotlin!\")\n}",
  "language": "KOTLIN",
  "expiration": "1d",
  "isPrivate": false
}

### Create paste - Password protected
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/paste
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Secret Paste",
  "content": "This is a secret message",
  "language": "TEXT",
  "password": "secret123",
  "expiration": "1w",
  "isPrivate": true
}

### Create paste - Minimal required fields (only content is required)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/paste
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Just content, no title"
}

### Create paste - Invalid (empty content - expects 400 Bad Request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/paste
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Empty Content",
  "content": ""
}

### Get paste by ID - Public paste
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/paste/abc123
Accept: application/json

### Get paste by ID - With password
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/paste/def456?password=secret123
Accept: application/json

### Get paste by ID - Wrong password
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/paste/def456?password=wrongpassword
Accept: application/json

### Get paste by ID - Not found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/paste/nonexistent
Accept: application/json

### Get paste by ID - Invalid ID format
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/paste/
Accept: application/json